A year ago today was the day I realized the people I loved, didn’t love me back the same.

This wasn’t the first time I had experienced violence in my life, in fact quite the opposite. 

I know I struggle sometimes and I push people away to save myself from the hurt, but what people often fail to see is that it’s a painful process building yourself back up and relearning who you are.

I never thought I’d say this but despite all I lost, I gained some valuable lessons through this. Mental resilience, actions always speak louder than words, overcoming my inner dialogue, patience, dealing with my emotions, will power, a new perspective.

The most distressing thought I had at the time was if I would ever be able to trust or love anyone again. And now 365 days later; I love myself, I love my friends, I love the life I’m creating for myself, and I know I’m capable of loving much more.

This is just the beginning.

2023年のルール決めました！

①毎日「生きててよかったじゃん！」って言う。辛い時も幸せな時も含めて人生だ。何があってもこれからも本当に生きててよかったじゃん 😇

②「すればよかったー」って後悔しないように先に行動して、後で考える。やりたいことや言いたいことは考えすぎると大体やらない時おおくって、やって失敗した方が習えるし素直に生きた方が心も落ち着く

③色んな生き方や考え方があるので他の人の考えや生き方は受け入れること。

④たまにはルール破ってもいいこと。ルールってたまあには守らない方が正しい時もある。たとえば会社のルールで働きすぎてメンタルヘルスがやられるより早めに帰るとか😇「この世界のこと誰が決めたことなの？何でこうなの？」って興味持て質問して自分で決めたい。他の国は違う生き方や法律でも幸せに生きてるじゃん？それだったら色んなルールとか色んな生き方あるから落ち着いて生きてもいいんじゃないかな？とりあえず素直で自由が一番心にいいと思う！このルールもその中に入る😂

今年はその4つだけ、人生はシンプルに生きてみよ✨

2023年もよろしくー！

Organizing the workflow ✍🏻

Life has been so crazy recently & I’ve been feeling so overwhelmed & pulled in so many directions that I was starting to struggle a lot.

Then I remembered a time when I wasn’t getting booked & I prayed for the days I would be so busy I could barely sit. When I first started my career in entertainment years ago, it was so slow because I was just getting my footing & had no experience. I went months without any work, countless auditions, & hundreds of rejections. I saw tons of the girls I started with quit the industry & lose hope.

I told myself I never wanted to be in that place again & I would do anything to change my life. 

So today when I woke up I told myself I’m not tired, I’m not exhausted, I’m not even stressed because these are all things I asked for. I can handle it & I will be even busier in the future - & if that’s the case I better enjoy how busy I am now. I’m lucky to work on so many things & passions of mine. I’m lucky I get to choose to work towards my dreams everyday. & of course I will feel tired at times but mindset really is everything. I am so grateful ☺️✨

I finished my first script!

Ever since I moved back to the US, I feel that my voice has finally started to emerge again.

I was afraid to tell my stories and speak up for myself in the past. I was told that having a strong opinion on topics would be bad for my image and that being silent was better. But all those worries have melted away as I saw the people around me be brave and vulnerable to share their experiences with me.

I felt inspired. And I want to inspire too ☺️

No human being is perfect and no one’s story is exactly the same. Telling stories close to you can be scary, but the more we share the experiences that shaped our lives, maybe that’ll help us all feel more comfortable embracing ourselves and our voices.

Just another day at the office 💋

I was a bit stuck in my head this week about writing and whether my scripts would be any good…. 

The creative process is tricky - we don’t have traditional work schedules or milestones to see where we are in our career, it’s against everything I grew up thinking was successful 😂

Not to mention, trying to start something in front of everyone I know is intimidating and I have doubts at times. But I’m really lucky to have friends who believe in me so much that they get angry when I doubt myself 🥹

I know it’s normal to have mental lows here and there, as long as I decide to keep writing and keep creating because it’s what I love doing 🥰

I’m really excited about this next script and I hope you all see my vision soon!
